# DFA Minimization System – Implementation Plan

A full-stack web application for inputting, validating, minimizing, and visualizing Deterministic Finite Automata. The frontend is React + Vite + Tailwind CSS; the backend is Node.js + Express.

## Proposed Changes

### 1. Project Setup

#### Frontend (existing `Sem-Project/`)
- Install: `react-router-dom`, `axios`, `tailwindcss @tailwindcss/vite`
- Add Tailwind Vite plugin to [vite.config.js](file:///c:/Users/Lenovo/Documents/Sem-IV%20Project/Sem-Project/vite.config.js)
- Replace [index.css](file:///c:/Users/Lenovo/Documents/Sem-IV%20Project/Sem-Project/src/index.css) with Tailwind directives + custom design tokens

#### [NEW] Backend (`Sem-Project/backend/`)
- `npm init -y`, install: `express`, `cors`, `nodemon`
- Add `"dev": "nodemon server.js"` script

---

### 2. Backend – Algorithm & API

#### [NEW] [minimizeDFA.js](file:///c:/Users/Lenovo/Documents/Sem-IV%20Project/Sem-Project/backend/algorithms/minimizeDFA.js)
Core algorithm module exporting:
- **`validateDFA(dfa)`** – checks states, alphabet, deterministic transitions, valid start/final states. Returns `{ valid, errors[] }`.
- **`removeUnreachableStates(dfa)`** – BFS from start state; removes unreachable states and their transitions.
- **`minimizeDFA(dfa)`** – Hopcroft-style partition refinement:
  1. Initial partition: `{finalStates, nonFinalStates}`
  2. Iteratively split partitions when two states in the same group transition to different groups on the same symbol
  3. Track each iteration as a `partitionStep` object `{ step, partitions, description }`
  4. Build minimized DFA (new states, transitions, start, finals)
  5. Return `{ reachableStates, partitionSteps, minimizedDFA }`

#### [NEW] [dfaController.js](file:///c:/Users/Lenovo/Documents/Sem-IV%20Project/Sem-Project/backend/controllers/dfaController.js)
- `minimizeHandler(req, res)` – validates input, calls algorithm, returns JSON response.

#### [NEW] [dfaRoutes.js](file:///c:/Users/Lenovo/Documents/Sem-IV%20Project/Sem-Project/backend/routes/dfaRoutes.js)
- `POST /api/minimize` → `minimizeHandler`

#### [NEW] [server.js](file:///c:/Users/Lenovo/Documents/Sem-IV%20Project/Sem-Project/backend/server.js)
- Express app on port 5000, cors enabled, JSON body parser, mounts routes.

